<knowl mode="exercise" xmlns="https://spatext.clontz.org" version="0.2">
    <intro>
        <p>
            {{prompt}} </p>
            
            <p><m>\quad\displaystyle {{dv}} = {{f}}\bigl( \, {{iv}} \, \bigr) \quad \text{ where } \quad {{f}}\bigl({{iv}}\bigr) = {{expr}}</m>, and</p>
            <p><m>\quad {{iv}}</m> denotes the {{ivd}}, measured in {{ivu}}, and </p>
            <p><m>\quad {{dv}}</m> denotes the {{dvd}}, measured in {{dvu}}.</p>
        
        <p> Translate each of the following into a complete sentence that would describe its practical interpretation. (Note that their values might not make "real-life" sense!)
        </p>
    </intro>
    
    <knowl>
    <content>
        <p> The equation <m>{{dv0}} = {{f}}\bigl({{iv0}}\bigr).</m>
            </p>
        </content>
    <outtro><p> When {{ivd}} is <m>{{iv0}}</m> {{ivu}}, then {{dvd}} is <m>{{dv0}}</m> {{dvu}}.
                </p>
        </outtro></knowl>

    <knowl>
    <content>
        <p> The value of <m>{{f}}\bigl({{iv1}}\bigr ).</m> (Compute this value before you explain.)
            </p>
        </content>
    <outtro><p> We have <m>{{f}}({{iv1}}) = {{dv1}}</m>.</p>
                <p> When {{ivd}} is <m>{{iv1}}</m> {{ivu}}, then {{dvd}} is <m>{{dv1}}</m> {{dvu}}.
                </p>
        </outtro></knowl>

    <knowl>
    <content>
        <p> The value of <m>{{iv}}</m> for which <m>{{dv2}} = {{f}}\bigl({{iv}}\bigr).</m> (You do <em>not</em> need to find this value, only explain what it would mean.)</p>
        </content>
    <outtro><p> This value of <m>{{iv}}</m> would represent the (unknown) {{ivd}} at which the {{dvd}} is <m>{{dv2}}</m> {{dvu}}.
                </p>
        </outtro></knowl>
</knowl>
